didn't hear this from me.

00:00:25.775 --> 00:00:27.819 position:50% align:center
But there are no records
of Shadow that I can find

00:00:27.902 --> 00:00:30.155 position:50% align:center
anywhere in the
central database.

00:00:30.238 --> 00:00:31.489 position:50% align:center
It's odd.

00:00:31.573 --> 00:00:33.283 position:50% align:center
Especially when you factor
in long-standing rumors

00:00:33.366 --> 00:00:35.702 position:50% align:center
among the police
regarding their existence.

00:00:35.785 --> 00:00:39.581 position:50% align:center
It's mostly speculation, but one
claim seems highly credible.

00:00:40.915 --> 00:00:42.375 position:50% align:center
[REIICHIROU]
Shadow's not a group.

00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:45.837 position:50% align:center
He's one person.

00:00:46.755 --> 00:00:47.922 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Really?

00:00:48.006 --> 00:00:50.091 position:50% align:center
Listen. I'm hearing some
reports coming in from

00:00:50.175 --> 00:00:52.844 position:50% align:center
the Juvenile and Community
Safety Divisions.

00:00:52.927 --> 00:00:55.889 position:50% align:center
It sounds like there could be
more trouble heading your way.

00:00:55.972 --> 00:00:58.433 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO] Yeah, I guess
you could say that.

00:00:58.516 --> 00:01:00.977 position:50% align:center
I'm just making sure that
you're not in over your head.

00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:03.897 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Yeah, yeah. I'll be careful.

00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:06.775 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh. Stay in touch, I got it.

00:01:07.776 --> 00:01:11.488 position:50% align:center
Why the heck is everyone
getting so worried about me?

00:01:11.571 --> 00:01:13.698 position:50% align:center
I mean, what am I?
A freakin' toddler?

00:01:15.658 --> 00:01:17.869 position:50% align:center
[TELLER] The number you have
dialed is either outside

00:01:17.952 --> 00:01:21.247 position:50% align:center
its service area or belongs
to an unpowered device.

00:01:21.331 --> 00:01:22.707 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Not again.

00:02:56.718 --> 00:02:58.303 position:50% align:center
[TOSHIAKI]
Okay, cut.

00:02:58.386 --> 00:03:00.013 position:50% align:center
Let's all take ten!

00:03:00.096 --> 00:03:02.015 position:50% align:center
[CREWMAN A]
It was a perfect sneak attack.

00:03:02.098 --> 00:03:03.933 position:50% align:center
[CREWMAN B]
You gotta be kidding.

00:03:04.017 --> 00:03:05.226 position:50% align:center
Not again.

00:03:05.310 --> 00:03:07.395 position:50% align:center
You still at it with
that making-of doc?

00:03:07.479 --> 00:03:09.272 position:50% align:center
Aren't we supposed
to be on a break?

00:03:09.356 --> 00:03:10.482 position:50% align:center
It's a big deal!

00:03:10.565 --> 00:03:12.400 position:50% align:center
You don't get to shoot
these every day.

00:03:12.484 --> 00:03:14.652 position:50% align:center
[CREWWOMAN A] Hey boss, can
you take a look at the dailies?

00:03:14.736 --> 00:03:16.154 position:50% align:center
Be right there!

00:03:16.237 --> 00:03:17.405 position:50% align:center
[CREWMAN A]
Oh.

00:03:17.489 --> 00:03:19.532 position:50% align:center
Man, Makoto.
You're getting really good.

00:03:19.616 --> 00:03:20.450 position:50% align:center
You absolutely killed it.

00:03:20.533 --> 00:03:22.118 position:50% align:center
You keep killing it every time.

00:03:22.202 --> 00:03:24.162 position:50% align:center
Oh, thanks, you guys.

00:03:24.245 --> 00:03:26.414 position:50% align:center
[CREWMAN A] Hey, we should
go out for drinks sometime.

00:03:26.498 --> 00:03:28.041 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Yeah. Totally.

00:03:31.336 --> 00:03:33.588 position:50% align:center
[TELLER] The number you
have dialed is either outside...

00:03:33.672 --> 00:03:34.923 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
C'mon, you jerk.

00:03:37.676 --> 00:03:40.387 position:50% align:center
What's the matter? King still
not answering his phone?

00:03:40.470 --> 00:03:43.056 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Figures.

00:03:43.139 --> 00:03:44.933 position:50% align:center
So, did you get a chance
to pass the new intel

00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:46.142 position:50% align:center
on to Hiroto?

00:03:46.226 --> 00:03:47.519 position:50% align:center
I did.

00:03:47.602 --> 00:03:49.729 position:50% align:center
But he said that whether
Shadow was working alone

00:03:49.813 --> 00:03:52.065 position:50% align:center
or as a group, it wouldn't
change a thing.

00:03:52.148 --> 00:03:53.233 position:50% align:center
Listen.

00:03:53.316 --> 00:03:54.401 position:50% align:center
Call him again and
tell him that Shadow's

00:03:54.484 --> 00:03:56.319 position:50% align:center
a one-man operation.

00:03:56.403 --> 00:03:58.154 position:50% align:center
The ones responsible
for attacking his people

00:03:58.238 --> 00:03:59.614 position:50% align:center
are imposters.

00:03:59.698 --> 00:04:01.533 position:50% align:center
Until we know who's
actually behind this,

00:04:01.616 --> 00:04:03.076 position:50% align:center
he needs to chill out.

00:04:03.159 --> 00:04:04.285 position:50% align:center
[CROW]
Right.

00:04:06.621 --> 00:04:07.747 position:50% align:center
It's Crow.

00:04:07.831 --> 00:04:09.582 position:50% align:center
Yeah hey, put me on
with Hiroto, will you?

00:04:09.666 --> 00:04:11.084 position:50% align:center
Hiroto could just talk to me,

00:04:11.167 --> 00:04:14.546 position:50% align:center
but instead he wants
to act all dramatic.

00:04:14.629 --> 00:04:16.214 position:50% align:center
Doesn't he know
he's not king yet?

00:04:19.217 --> 00:04:20.760 position:50% align:center
Oh, it's you.

00:04:20.844 --> 00:04:22.303 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Yup, it's me.

00:04:22.387 --> 00:04:23.555 position:50% align:center
Find anything new?

00:04:23.638 --> 00:04:25.515 position:50% align:center
Say, this stuff is delicious.

00:04:25.598 --> 00:04:27.600 position:50% align:center
You heard of this new
pudding made for dudes?

00:04:27.684 --> 00:04:30.270 position:50% align:center
It's pretty good.
You should get on that if not.

00:04:30.353 --> 00:04:31.813 position:50% align:center
You'll be sad you missed out!

00:04:34.566 --> 00:04:35.608 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Well?

00:04:35.692 --> 00:04:36.735 position:50% align:center
[SARU sighs]

00:04:36.818 --> 00:04:40.447 position:50% align:center
I found out which
people hired Shadow.

00:04:40.530 --> 00:04:43.033 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Wait. You mean it was a group?

00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:44.325 position:50% align:center
[SARU]
That's right.

00:04:44.409 --> 00:04:46.244 position:50% align:center
It's the shell company
for Northern Kanto's

00:04:46.327 --> 00:04:51.124 position:50% align:center
Maruken Sougyou.
Mars Enterprises.

00:04:51.207 --> 00:04:54.586 position:50% align:center
It seems they have expansion
plans for Ikebukuro.

00:04:54.669 --> 00:04:56.796 position:50% align:center
Plus, there's beef with
Donglong over turf lines

00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:58.590 position:50% align:center
in the red-light district.

00:04:58.673 --> 00:05:01.634 position:50% align:center
Some argument over
talent poaching.

00:05:01.718 --> 00:05:03.386 position:50% align:center
Sounds about right.

00:05:03.470 --> 00:05:05.472 position:50% align:center
[SARU] Weren't the guys who got
jumped at that Chinese joint

00:05:05.555 --> 00:05:07.015 position:50% align:center
Donglong too?

00:05:07.098 --> 00:05:08.516 position:50% align:center
They were.

00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.852 position:50% align:center
Honestly, something's
not adding up.

00:05:10.935 --> 00:05:12.103 position:50% align:center
[SARU]
Go on.

00:05:12.187 --> 00:05:13.772 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
One of my sources filled me in.

00:05:13.855 --> 00:05:17.108 position:50% align:center
Shadow's a solo artist,
not a gang.

00:05:17.192 --> 00:05:18.818 position:50% align:center
[SARU]
Huh. Interesting.

00:05:18.902 --> 00:05:20.070 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Meanwhile,

00:05:20.153 --> 00:05:21.738 position:50% align:center
the random douchebags
attacking Hiroto's men

00:05:21.821 --> 00:05:24.657 position:50% align:center
are going by the same name.
It's weird.

00:05:27.243 --> 00:05:28.870 position:50% align:center
[SARU] There's a chance
that Mars is playing a part

00:05:28.953 --> 00:05:30.163 position:50% align:center
in this too.

00:05:30.246 --> 00:05:31.831 position:50% align:center
Remember what I
said the other day?

00:05:31.915 --> 00:05:33.291 position:50% align:center
It's all about balance.

00:05:34.709 --> 00:05:36.461 position:50% align:center
If they want to gain influence,

00:05:36.544 --> 00:05:38.046 position:50% align:center
it's in their best interest
to make trouble

00:05:38.129 --> 00:05:39.798 position:50% align:center
for the Hidaka Group.

00:05:39.881 --> 00:05:41.883 position:50% align:center
After all, you gotta rock
the boat if you wanna

00:05:41.966 --> 00:05:43.259 position:50% align:center
command the ship.

00:05:45.762 --> 00:05:47.222 position:50% align:center
In that regard,

00:05:47.305 --> 00:05:50.392 position:50% align:center
I suppose that everything's
proceeding according to plan.

00:05:50.475 --> 00:05:51.810 position:50% align:center
Gotcha.

00:05:51.893 --> 00:05:54.521 position:50% align:center
So that's what the real
troublemakers are after, huh?

00:05:54.604 --> 00:05:56.314 position:50% align:center
Hey, thanks for all your help

00:05:56.398 --> 00:05:57.357 position:50% align:center
[SARU]
Hey, no problem.

00:05:57.440 --> 00:05:59.484 position:50% align:center
I went ahead
and told Takashi too.

00:05:59.567 --> 00:06:00.652 position:50% align:center
Later.

00:06:01.945 --> 00:06:04.155 position:50% align:center
So you'll answer
Saru but not me?

00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:07.575 position:50% align:center
[MAN]
Don't move.

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:13.581 position:50% align:center
Makoto Majima.
Do you know who I am?

00:06:13.665 --> 00:06:15.125 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Should I?

00:06:15.208 --> 00:06:17.711 position:50% align:center
[MAN] Let's just say I've
got a bone to pick.

00:06:17.794 --> 00:06:19.838 position:50% align:center
Because destroying the
G-Boys is more than some

00:06:19.921 --> 00:06:22.132 position:50% align:center
petty turf war.

00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:24.676 position:50% align:center
What I'm really after is power.

00:06:24.759 --> 00:06:26.720 position:50% align:center
So get ready to bow down.

00:06:26.803 --> 00:06:28.972 position:50% align:center
Do you even hear
yourself right now?

00:06:29.055 --> 00:06:31.474 position:50% align:center
They aren't gonna
take this sitting down.

00:06:33.393 --> 00:06:35.478 position:50% align:center
[MAN] Don't worry,
I'll get my revenge.

00:06:38.732 --> 00:06:40.567 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO grunting]

00:06:51.244 --> 00:06:53.455 position:50% align:center
[TOSHIAKI]
Makoto! Wake up already!

00:06:55.290 --> 00:06:56.583 position:50% align:center
Hey, are you all right?

00:06:56.666 --> 00:06:57.667 position:50% align:center
You were out.

00:06:57.751 --> 00:06:59.711 position:50% align:center
Bedtime's over, sleepyhead.

00:06:59.794 --> 00:07:01.379 position:50% align:center
We need to finish shooting.

00:07:01.463 --> 00:07:04.341 position:50% align:center
At this rate, the store'll close
before we can wrap production.

00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:08.845 position:50% align:center
Some guy in a rabbit
mask attacked me.

00:07:08.928 --> 00:07:10.388 position:50% align:center
That sounds creepy.

00:07:10.472 --> 00:07:13.016 position:50% align:center
Actually, that would
make a great movie pitch.

00:07:15.393 --> 00:07:18.271 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Toshiaki. Is that camera on?

00:07:18.355 --> 00:07:20.482 position:50% align:center
[TOSHIAKI] Yeah. It should
still be recording.

00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:26.321 position:50% align:center
Okay. Lemme know
when you're done here.

00:07:26.404 --> 00:07:27.864 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
We will. Thanks.

00:07:29.282 --> 00:07:32.160 position:50% align:center
If this works, then we'll
know who the guy was.

00:07:32.243 --> 00:07:33.745 position:50% align:center
Whoa, you're a genius.

00:07:33.828 --> 00:07:36.122 position:50% align:center
Crushin' it as a detective
and an indie actor.

00:07:39.793 --> 00:07:42.504 position:50% align:center
[MAN] Let's just say I've
got a bone to pick.

00:07:42.587 --> 00:07:44.631 position:50% align:center
Because destroying the
G-Boys is more than some

00:07:44.714 --> 00:07:47.050 position:50% align:center
petty turf war.

00:07:47.133 --> 00:07:49.219 position:50% align:center
What I'm really after is power.

